snippet.textDisplay:
TIPS are essential but remember that CoV-SARS-2 (the CoViD-19 virus) can survive on surfaces for several days and handling money is a potential means of spreading the virus. If you are paying/tipping, do it over electronic platforms when possible and avoid the need for change. If you are receiving the money, remember to sanitize your hands and to avoid close contact. 
Also remember that the number of confirmed cases may be lagging the actual numbers by one to two weeks due to the non-symptomatic period (incubation). This means that the actual number of cases may be 10 to 100 times higher already (world trend of 10x increase per week before preventive measures were taken).
Best of luck from a shutdown Portugal.

If you are paying/tipping, do it over electronic platforms when possible and avoid the need for change. If you are receiving the money, remember to sanitize your hands and to avoid close contact. 
Also remember that the number of confirmed cases may be lagging the actual numbers by one to two weeks due to the non-symptomatic period (incubation).
